.TH DU-EXCLUDES 1 "June 2026" "mx-remaster" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
du-excludes \- show disk usage for files listed in an exclude file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B du-excludes
.I exclude-file
.I directory
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B du-excludes
reads a list of file or directory names from an exclude file and runs
.B du
against the named paths after prepending the supplied directory.
It is a convenience tool used by the remaster workflow to estimate how much
space files will consume on a different filesystem or mount point.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show the help text and exit.
.PP
The script also accepts the legacy
.B -help
spelling.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I exclude-file
File containing one path per line.
.TP
.I directory
Directory prefix added to each entry before running
.BR du .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B du-excludes /live/config/remaster.exclude /mnt/target
Estimate the space used by the files listed in
.I /live/config/remaster.exclude
relative to
.IR /mnt/target .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR du (1),
.BR live-remaster (1),
.BR installed-to-live (1)
.SH AUTHOR
mx-remaster maintainers
